# KindleHub Pro — HTTP security headers
#
# This file is honoured automatically by Cloudflare Pages and Netlify. If the
# site is served some other way (a plain static host proxied through
# Cloudflare), set the same headers with a Cloudflare Transform Rule instead —
# see SECURITY.md for the copy-paste steps. The <meta> CSP and referrer tags in
# index.html already cover browsers regardless of host; the directives BELOW are
# the ones a <meta> tag cannot express (HSTS, X-Frame-Options, nosniff,
# Permissions-Policy, frame-ancestors), so they must be real response headers.

/*
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self' https: data: blob:; script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' 'unsafe-eval' https://cdn.jsdelivr.net; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self' data: blob: https:; font-src 'self' data:; connect-src 'self' https:; media-src 'self' data: blob: https:; frame-src 'self' data: blob: https:; worker-src 'self' blob:; object-src 'none'; base-uri 'self'; frame-ancestors 'none'
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: accelerometer=(), camera=(), geolocation=(self), gyroscope=(), magnetometer=(), microphone=(), payment=(), usb=()
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
  X-Permitted-Cross-Domain-Policies: none

# ── Caching (perf) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The app HTML is big; make repeat visits cheap WITHOUT ever serving a stale
# build. must-revalidate + max-age=0 means the Kindle asks "changed?" (a tiny
# request) and, when it hasn't, gets a 304 and reuses its cached copy instead of
# re-downloading the whole file. On deploy you still Purge Everything as usual.
/
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate
/index.html
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate
# Static assets rarely change — cache them hard so they never re-download.
/icon.svg
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=604800
/*.png
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=604800
/*.svg
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=604800
/*.js
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=86400
